14\n| 5 August 2011\n| 7 May 2014\n| [[Yingluck Shinawatra]]\n| ''Common-law husband''\n|-\n| 27\n| Assoc. Prof. Naraporn Chan-o-cha<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/news/politics/428293/general-gets-ready-to-swap-into-civvies|title=General gets ready to swap into civvies|author=Wassana Nanuam|date=August 23, 2014|work= |newspaper=Bangkok Post|accessdate=November 10, 2014}}</ref><br>{{lang|th|\u0e23\u0e28.\u0e19\u0e23\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23 \u0e08\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e42\u0e2d\u0e0a\u0e32}}\n| Rotchanachan<br>{{lang|th|\u0e42\u0e23\u0e08\u0e19\u0e08\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e23\u0e4c}}\n| 24 August 2014\n| Incumbent\n| [[Prayut Chan-o-cha]]\n| \n|}\n\n==Living Spouses of the former Prime Ministers==\nAs of {{Monthyear}}, there are twelve living Spouses of the former Prime Ministers, as seen below.\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:No Picture.jpg| [[Wirat Chamanan]]<br />served 1973\u20131980<br />born 5 Dec 1927 (age {{age|1927|12|5}})<br />wife of [[Kriangsak Chamanan]]\nFile:No Picture.jpg| [[Bunruean Choonhavan]]<br />served 1988\u20131991<br />born 25 Apr 1919 (age {{age|1919|4|25}})<br />wife of [[Chatichai Choonhavan]]\nFile:No Picture.jpg| [[Sotsi Panyarachun]]<br />served 1991\u20131992<br />born 21 Jul 1936 (age {{age|1936|7|21}})<br />wife of [[Anand Panyarachun]]\nFile:No Picture.jpg| [[Wanni Kraprayoon]]<br />served 1992<br />born 15 May 1939 (age {{age|1939|5|15}})<br />wife of [[Suchinda Kraprayoon]]\nFile:No Picture.jpg| [[Phakdiphon Sucharitakul]]<br />served 1st: 1992\u20131995<br />2nd: 1997\u20132001<br />born 20 Aug 1954 (age {{age|1954|8|20}})<br />wife of [[Chuan Leekpai]]\nFile:No Picture.jpg| [[Jamsai Silpa-archa]]<br />served 1995\u20131996<br />born 20 Apr 1934 (age {{age|1934|4|20}})<br />wife of [[Banharn Silpa-archa]]\nFile:No Picture.jpg| Phankhruea Yongchaiyudh<br />served 1996\u20131997<br />born 20 Jan 1939 (age {{age|1939|1|20}})<br />wife of [[Chavalit Yongchaiyudh]]\nFile:No Picture.jpg| [[Potjaman Na Pombejra]]<b