{"title_page": "Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name            = Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology (BAUST)\n| native_name     = \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6 \u0986\u09b0\u09cd\u09ae\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u099c\u09cd\u099e\u09be\u09a8 \u0993 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u09ac\u09ac\u09bf\u09a6\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09b2\u09af\u09bc(\u09ac\u09bf\u098f\u0987\u0989\u098f\u09b8\u099f\u09bf)\n| image           = BAUST logo.jpeg\n| image_size      = \n| motto           = Discipline, Knowledge, Morality\n| type            = Bangladesh Army administrated   university\n| established     = {{Start date|February 2015}}\n| chancellor      = [[President of Bangladesh]]\n| vice_chancellor = [[Brigadier General]] Professor Dr Md Lutfor Rahman (LPR)\n| students        = \n| undergrad       = \n| postgrad        = \n| doctoral        = \n| address         = [[Saidpur Cantonment]]\n| city            = [[Saidpur, Bangladesh|Saidpur]]\n| country         = [[Bangladesh]]\n| coordinates     = {{coord|25.7631|88.9175|type:edu_region:BD|display=inline,title}}\n| campus          = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n| colors          = {{Color box|Green|border=darkgray}} {{Color box|#FFDF00|border=darkgray}}<br />Green and Golden\n| website         = {{URL|baust.edu.bd}}\n}}\n\n'''Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology''' ('''BAUST''') ({{lang-bn|\u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6 \u0986\u09b0\u09cd\u09ae\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u099c\u09cd\u099e\u09be\u09a8 \u0993 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u09ac\u09ac\u09bf\u09a6\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09b2\u09af\u09bc }}) is an [[Bangladesh Army|army]]-backed  university in [[Saidpur, Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ugc.gov.bd/en/home/university/private/75 |title=List of Private Universities |website=University Grants Commission of Bangladesh |access-date=2016-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828051935/http://www.ugc.gov.bd/en/home/university/private/75 |archive-date=2018-08-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Army to get three universities |url=http://www.en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/56600/Army-to-get-three-universities |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=November 27, 2014 |access-date=2016-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827163155/http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/56600/Army-to-get-three-universities |archive-date=August 27, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.baust.edu.bd/pages/content_details/baust-at-a-glance-2 |title=BAUST at a Glance |website=Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nBangladesh Army University of Science and Technology is one of the three private universities run by [[Bangladesh Army]]; approved by Prime Minister [[Sheikh Hasina]] on February 12, 2015. On February 15, 2015 It was inaugurated by [[Asaduzzaman Noor]], former Minister of Cultural Affairs Ministry of Bangladesh in the presence of senior army officers of Bangladesh Army.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bangla.bdnews24.com/bangladesh/article925382.bdnews |title=Army University in Nilphamari launched|website=Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\n[[File:BAUST Main Campus.jpg|thumb|left|Main Academic Building of BAUST]]\nThe main campus is located in [[Saidpur, Bangladesh|Saidpur]] with infrastructure support from [[Saidpur Cantonment]]. Saidpur is a town of [[Nilphamari]] district in Bangladesh, part of the [[Rangpur Division]]. [[Saidpur Airport]] is very close to the university campus.\n{{clear-left}}\n\n== Faculties ==\n[[File:Baust Back view.jpg|thumb|right|BAUST back view]]\n[[File:From Office view.jpg|thumb|right]]\n[[File:Baust Back view 2.jpg|thumb|right|BAUST Campus]]\n\n4 years B.Sc. Undergraduate Courses and Engineering Courses\n\n===Faculty of Electrical and Computer Engineering (ECE)===\n* Department of [[Electrical & Electronic Engineering]]\n*Department of [[Computer Science & Engineering]]\n\n===Faculty of Mechanical & Production Engineering (MPE)===\n* Department of [[Mechanical Engineering]]\n* Department of [[Industrial and production engineering|Industrial & Production Engineering]]\n\n===Faculty of Civil Engineering(CE)===\n* Department of [[Civil Engineering]]\n\n=== Faculty of Business Studies ===\n* Department of [[Business Administration]]\n\n=== Faculty of Science & Humanities ===\n* Department of English\n* Department of Arts and Sciences\n\n== Regulatory bodies ==\n\n=== <u>Academic Council of BAUST</u> ===\n\n==== Chairman ====\n* Vice Chancellor, Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology\n\n==== Members ====\n* Pro Vice Chancellor\n* All Deans\n* All Department/Institute Heads\n* One Professor from Each Department\n* Three Education Patron Nominated by Board of Trustees\n* Two Educationalist Nominated by Syndicate\n\n==== Member secretary ====\n* Registrar, BAUST\n\n==Student life==\nTo break the monotony of study different cultural programs are arranged at regular intervals.\n\n==Student's dress==\nIt is mandatory for students to wear dress with displayed identity card as per 'Dress Code' prescribed by BAUST authority.\n\n== Halls of residence ==\nBAUST has individual halls for male and female students. Hostel administration is performed by the provost who is selected from one of the senior teachers of the all departments or Ex-Army Officer.\n\n===Abbas Uddin Ahmed Hall===\nAbbas Uddin Ahmed Hall (A U Ahmed Hall) is named after [[Abbasuddin Ahmed]], the famous folk artist of Bangladesh. A U Ahmed Hall is a 4 storied building with only male students, having a capacity of 500 students. There are 20 staffs for hall. A U Ahmed Hall is known for the security of the students compared to the other hall in the country. Students get various modern facilities such as 24-hour electricity, 24/7 internet service, gym, games and sports facilities. Annual hall festival is being celebrated in November of every year. Moreover, A U Ahmed hall provides the best hall facility in this country.\n\n===Taramon Bibi Hall===\nTaramon Bibi Hall is named after Bir Protik [[Taramon Bibi]], one of the two female freedom fighters in Bangladesh who had engaged in direct combat during the [[liberation war of Bangladesh]] in 1971 as a member of the Mukti Bahini (Liberation Army). Taramon Bibi hall is an 2 storied building with only female students, having a capacity of 300 students. There are 20 staffs for hall. As A U Ahmed Hall, it is also known for the security of the students compared to the other hall in the country. Annual hall festival is being celebrated in November of every year like A U Ahmed Hall.\n\n== Students organizations ==\n\n* Career Society of BAUST\n* ''BAUST''  Robotics Society\n* ''BAUST''  Cultural Club\n* ''BAUST''  Debating Society\n* ''BAUST''  Photographic Eye\n* ''BAUST''  CSE Society\n* ''BAUST''  IT Forum\n* Radio BAUST (in progress)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website|http://www.baust.edu.bd}}\n* [http://www.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/article/1039805/\u0987\u099e\u09cd\u099c\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u0982-\u09ac\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0-\u09ae\u09cb\u09a1\u09bc\u0995-\u0989\u09a8\u09cd\u09ae\u09cb\u099a\u09a8 \u0987\u099e\u09cd\u099c\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u0982-\u09ac\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0-\u09ae\u09cb\u09a1\u09bc\u0995-\u0989\u09a8\u09cd\u09ae\u09cb\u099a\u09a8]\n* [http://www.prothom-alo.com/education/article/1195701/ \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf-\u0993-\u0989\u09ce\u09b8\u09ac\u09c7\u09b0-\u09a6\u09bf\u09a8]\n* [https://ca.eventbu.com/city/baust-eee-day-2018/8952845]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Army]]\n[[Category:Educational Institutions affiliated with Bangladesh Army]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name            = Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology (BAUST)\n| native_name     = \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6 \u0986\u09b0\u09cd\u09ae\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u099c\u09cd\u099e\u09be\u09a8 \u0993 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u09ac\u09ac\u09bf\u09a6\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09b2\u09af\u09bc(\u09ac\u09bf\u098f\u0987\u0989\u098f\u09b8\u099f\u09bf)\n| image           = BAUST logo.jpeg\n| image_size      = \n| motto           = Discipline, Knowledge, Morality\n| type            = Bangladesh Army administrated   university\n| established     = {{Start date|February 2015}}\n| chancellor      = [[President of Bangladesh]]\n| vice_chancellor = [[Brigadier General]] Professor Dr Md Lutfor Rahman (LPR)\n| students        = \n| undergrad       = \n| postgrad        = \n| doctoral        = \n| address         = [[Saidpur Cantonment]]\n| city            = [[Saidpur, Bangladesh|Saidpur]]\n| country         = [[Bangladesh]]\n| coordinates     = {{coord|25.7631|88.9175|type:edu_region:BD|display=inline,title}}\n| campus          = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n| colors          = {{Color box|Green|border=darkgray}} {{Color box|#FFDF00|border=darkgray}}<br />Green and Golden\n| website         = {{URL|baust.edu.bd}}\n}}\n\n'''Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology''' ('''BAUST''') ({{lang-bn|\u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6 \u0986\u09b0\u09cd\u09ae\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u099c\u09cd\u099e\u09be\u09a8 \u0993 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf \u09ac\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u09ac\u09ac\u09bf\u09a6\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09b2\u09af\u09bc }}) is an [[Bangladesh Army|army]]-backed  university in [[Saidpur, Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ugc.gov.bd/en/home/university/private/75 |title=List of Private Universities |website=University Grants Commission of Bangladesh |access-date=2016-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828051935/http://www.ugc.gov.bd/en/home/university/private/75 |archive-date=2018-08-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Army to get three universities |url=http://www.en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/56600/Army-to-get-three-universities |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=November 27, 2014 |access-date=2016-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827163155/http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/56600/Army-to-get-three-universities |archive-date=August 27, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.baust.edu.bd/pages/content_details/baust-at-a-glance-2 |title=BAUST at a Glance |website=Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nBangladesh Army University of Science and Technology is one of the three private universities run by [[Bangladesh Army]]; approved by Prime Minister [[Sheikh Hasina]] on February 12, 2015. On February 15, 2015 It was inaugurated by [[Asaduzzaman Noor]], former Minister of Cultural Affairs Ministry of Bangladesh in the presence of senior army officers of Bangladesh Army.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bangla.bdnews24.com/bangladesh/article925382.bdnews |title=Army University in Nilphamari launched|website=Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\n[[File:BAUST Main Campus.jpg|thumb|left|Main Academic Building of BAUST]]\nThe main campus is located in [[Saidpur, Bangladesh|Saidpur]] with infrastructure support from [[Saidpur Cantonment]]. Saidpur is a town of [[Nilphamari]] district in Bangladesh, part of the [[Rangpur Division]]. [[Saidpur Airport]] is very close to the university campus.\n{{clear-left}}\n\n== Faculties ==\n[[File:Baust Back view.jpg|thumb|right|BAUST back view]]\n[[File:From Office view.jpg|thumb|right]]\n[[File:Baust Back view 2.jpg|thumb|right|BAUST Campus]]\n\n4 years B.Sc. Undergraduate Courses and Engineering Courses\n\n===Faculty of Electrical and Computer Engineering (ECE)===\n* Department of [[Electrical & Electronic Engineering]]\n*Department of [[Computer Science & Engineering]]\n\n===Faculty of Mechanical & Production Engineering (MPE)===\n* Department of [[Mechanical Engineering]]\n* Department of [[Industrial and production engineering|Industrial & Production Engineering]]\n\n===Faculty of Civil Engineering(CE)===\n* Department of [[Civil Engineering]]\n\n=== Faculty of Business Studies ===\n* Department of [[Business Administration]]\n\n=== Faculty of Science & Humanities ===\n* Department of English\n* Department of Arts and Sciences\n\n== Regulatory bodies ==\n\n=== <u>Academic Council of BAUST</u> ===\n\n==== Chairman ====\n* Vice Chancellor, Bangladesh Army University of Science and Technology\n\n==== Members ====\n* Pro Vice Chancellor\n* All Deans\n* All Department/Institute Heads\n* One Professor from Each Department\n* Three Education Patron Nominated by Board of Trustees\n* Two Educationalist Nominated by Syndicate\n\n==== Member secretary ====\n* Registrar, BAUST\n\n==Student life==\nTo break the monotony of study different cultural programs are arranged at regular intervals.\n\n==Student's dress==\nIt is mandatory for students to wear dress with displayed identity card as per 'Dress Code' prescribed by BAUST authority.\n\n== Halls of residence ==\nBAUST has individual halls for male and female students. Hostel administration is performed by the provost who is selected from one of the senior teachers of the all departments or Ex-Army Officer.\n\n===Abbas Uddin Ahmed Hall===\nAbbas Uddin Ahmed Hall (A U Ahmed Hall) is named after [[Abbasuddin Ahmed]], the famous folk artist of Bangladesh. A U Ahmed Hall is a 4 storied building with only male students, having a capacity of 500 students. There are 20 staffs for hall. A U Ahmed Hall is known for the security of the students compared to the other hall in the country. Students get various modern facilities such as 24-hour electricity, 24/7 internet service, gym, games and sports facilities. Annual hall festival is being celebrated in November of every year. Moreover, A U Ahmed hall provides the best hall facility in this country.\n\n===Taramon Bibi Hall===\nTaramon Bibi Hall is named after Bir Protik [[Taramon Bibi]], one of the two female freedom fighters in Bangladesh who had engaged in direct combat during the [[liberation war of Bangladesh]] in 1971 as a member of the Mukti Bahini (Liberation Army). Taramon Bibi hall is an 2 storied building with only female students, having a capacity of 300 students. There are 20 staffs for hall. As A U Ahmed Hall, it is also known for the security of the students compared to the other hall in the country. Annual hall festival is being celebrated in November of every year like A U Ahmed Hall.\n\n== Students organizations ==\n\n* Career Society of BAUST\n* ''BAUST''  Robotics Society\n* ''BAUST''  Cultural Club\n* ''BAUST''  Debating Society\n* ''BAUST''  Photographic Eye\n* ''BAUST''  CSE Society\n* ''BAUST''  IT Forum\n* Radio BAUST (in progress)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website|http://www.baust.edu.bd}}\n* [http://www.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/article/1039805/\u0987\u099e\u09cd\u099c\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u0982-\u09ac\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0-\u09ae\u09cb\u09a1\u09bc\u0995-\u0989\u09a8\u09cd\u09ae\u09cb\u099a\u09a8 \u0987\u099e\u09cd\u099c\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u0982-\u09ac\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09b0-\u09ae\u09cb\u09a1\u09bc\u0995-\u0989\u09a8\u09cd\u09ae\u09cb\u099a\u09a8]\n* [http://www.prothom-alo.com/education/article/1195701/ \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09c1\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf-\u0993-\u0989\u09ce\u09b8\u09ac\u09c7\u09b0-\u09a6\u09bf\u09a8]\n* [https://ca.eventbu.com/city/baust-eee-day-2018/8952845]\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Army]]\n[[Category:Educational Institutions affiliated with Bangladesh Army]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh_Army_University_of_Science_and_Technology"}
