ter's degrees, and doctoral degrees.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of universities in Thailand]]\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.bkkthon.ac.th/}}\n\n{{Universities in Thailand}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2002]]\n[[Category:2002 establishments in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Universities in Thailand]]\n\n\n{{Thailand-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name            =Bangkokthonburi University\n|native_name     = \u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e01\u0e23\u0e38\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e1e\u0e18\u0e19\u0e1a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e35\n|latin_name      =\n|motto           = \u0e2a\u0e23\u0e49\u0e32\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e32 \u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e04\u0e19 \u0e1d\u0e36\u0e01\u0e1d\u0e19\u0e04\u0e38\u0e13\u0e18\u0e23\u0e23\u0e21\n|mottoeng = knowledge, wisdom, and morality\n|established     = 2002\n|type            = [[private university|Private]]\n|endowment       =\n|rector          =\n|chancellor      =\n|president       = Dr. Bangorn Benjathirkul\n|provost         =\n|vice_chancellor =\n|principal       = \n|dean            =\n|head_label      =\n|head            =\n|students        = over 10,000 (2016)\n|undergrad       =\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|city            = [[Thawi Watthana District|Thawi Watthana]], [[Bangkok]]\n|state           =\n|country         = [[Thailand]] \n|campus          = Bangkok\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|colours         =\n|nickname        = BTU\n|mascot          = \n|website         = [http://www.bkkthon.ac.th www.bkkthon.ac.th]\n| logo = \n| logo_size = \n|footnotes       =\n|image_name      =\n|staff           =\n|faculty         =\n|colors          = \n|affiliation    = \n|coor            = {{coord|13.769349|100.345516|format=dms|type:landmark_scale:3000}}\n}}\n\n'''Bangkokthonburi University''' is a higher education institute located in [[Thawi Watthana District]], [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]. Founded in 2002, the college offers [[undergraduate]] and [[Graduate school|graduate]] studies in [[business administration]], [[law]], [[political science]], [[science]], and [[education]].\n\n== Academic programs ==\nUsing Thai as the language of instruction, Bangkok University awards bachelor's degrees,  master's degrees, and doctoral degrees.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of universities in Thailand]]\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.bkkthon.ac.th/}}\n\n{{Universities in Thailand}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2002]]\n[[Category:2002 establishments in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Universities in Thailand]]\n\n\n{{Thailand-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangkokthonburi_University"}
{"title_page": "Bangkok University", "text_new": "{{distinguish|University of Bangkok Metropolis}}\n{{one source|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name            =Bangkok University\n|native_name     = \u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e01\u0e23\u0e38\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e1e\n|latin_name      =\n|motto           = \u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e23\u0e39\u0e49 \u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e14\u0e35\n|mottoeng = Knowledge with Virtue\n|established     = 1962\n|type            = [[private university|Private]]\n|endowment       =\n|rector          =\n|chancellor      =\n|president       = Mr Petch Osathanugrah\n|provost         =\n|vice_chancellor =\n|principal       = \n|dean            =\n|head_label      =\n|head            =\n|students        = over 28,000 (2008)\n|undergrad       =\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|city            = [[Bangkok]]\n|state           =\n|country         = [[Thailand]] \n|campus          = Bangkok, Rangsit\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|colours         =\n|nickname        = BU\n|mascot          = [[Cinnamomum aromaticum|Javanese Cassia tree]]\n|website         ={{URL|http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/}}\n| logo = BU Logo.png\n| logo_size = 250px\n|footnotes       =\n|image     = File:Bangkok Universit..Rangsit campus. - panoramio.jpg\n|image_name      = \n|staff           =\n|faculty         =\n|colors          = [[Orange (colour)|Orange]] & [[Purple]] {{color box|#FFA500}}{{color box|#800080}}\n|affiliation    = [[ASAIHL]]\n|coor            = {{coord|13|42|41.10|N|100|34|54.87|E|type:edu_region:TH|display=inline,title}}\n}}\n{{maplink|frame=yes|frame-width=240|zoom=13|type=point}}\n\n'''Bangkok University''' ({{lang-th|\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e01\u0e23\u0e38\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e1e}}), established in 1962, is one of the oldest and largest private, non-profit universities in Thailand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/en/about/history|title=History|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> The main campus is in the [[Khlong Toei District|central business district]] of Bangkok. The university expanded its operation to a second campus in [[Rangsit, Thailand|Rangsit]], [[Pathum Thani Province]] to accommodate its rapid growth.\n\nThe university president is Mr Petch Osathanugrah (2016).<ref>{{cite web|title=Executive Officer|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/about-executive-officer.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425134627/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/about-executive-officer.html|archive-date=25 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Academic programs ==\nUsing Thai as the language of instruction, Bangkok University awards bachelor's degrees,<ref>{{cite web|title=Bachelor's Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-bachelor-degree-normal-program.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321133556/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-bachelor-degree-normal-program.html|archive-date=21 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> master's degrees,<ref>{{cite web|title=Master's Degrees|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-master-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427175333/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-master-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> and doctoral degrees.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctoral Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-doctoral-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321020014/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-doctoral-degree.html|archive-date=21 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The university also has an international program,<ref>{{cite web|title=International Program|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-programs.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427175327/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-programs.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> using English as the language of instruction. The international program awards bachelor's,<ref>{{cite web|title=International Program; Bachelor Degree/ \u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e19\u0e32\u0e19\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e15\u0e34|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-bachelor-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427230047/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-bachelor-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> master's,<ref>{{cite web|title=Master Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-master-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321132301/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-master-degree.html|archive-date=21 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> and doctoral degrees.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctoral Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427230053/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Affiliates ==\n* BU Alumni<ref>{{cite web|title=BU Alumni|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/bu_alumni.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425152106/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/bu_alumni.html|archive-date=25 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Creative Entrepreneurship Development Institute<ref>{{cite web|title=Creative Entrepreneurship Development Institute|url=http://cedi.bu.ac.th/|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n* Bangkok University Research Center<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangkok University Research Center|url=http://bangkokpoll.bu.ac.th/|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n* The Institute for Knowledge and Innovation, Southeast Asia<ref>{{cite web|title=The Institute for Knowledge and Innovation, Southeast Asia|url=http://www.iki-sea.org/|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n*Center for Promotion of Human Resources\n*Institute of Research Promotion and Innovation Development\n*Institutional Research and Evaluation Office\n*Language Institute<ref>{{cite web|title=Language Institute|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427230053/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*Law Center for Citizens\n\n== Campuses ==\nBangkok University has two campuses:\n\n=== City campus ===\nThe city campus (called ''Kluay Nam Thai Campus'', {{lang-th|\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e40\u0e02\u0e15\u0e01\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27\u0e22\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e44\u0e17}}) is in [[Phra Khanong, Khlong Toei|Phra Khanong Sub-district]], [[Khlong Toei District]].<ref name=\"Contact BU\">{{cite web|title=Contact BU|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/contact-us.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425123026/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/contact-us.html|archive-date=25 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> It occupies approximately 15,000 m<sup>2</sup>. International students attend this campus, as well as academics in special programs. It is the campus for most students in their third or fourth years. It is the location of the office of the university president, as well as the international college, the graduate school, and other faculties. There are laboratories, classrooms, seminar rooms, libraries, computer centre, and an indoor sports centre. An art gallery, the Bangkok University Gallery (BUG), opened on the campus in 2006. Bangkok University has decided to close this campus in the near future, and move all operations to the Rangsit campus, now already called \"main campus\".\n\n=== Rangsit campus ===\nThe Rangsit campus (\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e40\u0e02\u0e15\u0e23\u0e31\u0e07\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e15) is in Khlong Neung Sub-district [[Khlong Luang District]] of Pathum Thani Province.<ref name=\"Contact BU\" /> It is approximately fourteen kilometres north of [[Don Mueang International Airport]]. The campus is approximately 265,000 m<sup>2</sup> in size. Regular students in their first and second years study here, except that regular communication arts students (not international) study on this campus for four years. Also on the campus are the Bangkok University Stadium, home stadium of [[Bangkok University FC]], [[Thailand Premier League 2006]] champions, the Surat Osathanugrah Library, and Pongtip Osathanugrah Communication Arts Complex. The BU Southeast Asian Ceramics Museum, an important archaeological research facility, is on the Rangsit campus. The campus meets the [[ISO14000#ISO 14001 standard|ISO 14001 standard]], the first in Thailand to do so.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Portal|Thailand}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20171129124320/http://www2.bu.ac.th/eng/ Bangkok University]\n*{{Commons category-inline|Bangkok University}}\n{{Universities in Thailand}}\n{{ASAIHL}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1962]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:Private universities and colleges in Thailand]]\n[[Category:1962 establishments in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Universities in Thailand]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|University of Bangkok Metropolis}}\n{{one source|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name            =Bangkok University\n|native_name     = \u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e01\u0e23\u0e38\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e1e\n|latin_name      =\n|motto           = \u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e23\u0e39\u0e49 \u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e14\u0e35\n|mottoeng = Knowledge with Virtue\n|established     = 1962\n|type            = [[private university|Private]]\n|endowment       =\n|rector          =\n|chancellor      =\n|president       = Mr Petch Osathanugrah\n|provost         =\n|vice_chancellor =\n|principal       = \n|dean            =\n|head_label      =\n|head            =\n|students        = over 28,000 (2008)\n|undergrad       =\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|city            = [[Bangkok]]\n|state           =\n|country         = [[Thailand]] \n|campus          = Bangkok, Rangsit\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|colours         =\n|nickname        = BU\n|mascot          = [[Cinnamomum aromaticum|Javanese Cassia tree]]\n|website         ={{URL|http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/}}\n| logo = BU Logo.png\n| logo_size = 250px\n|footnotes       =\n|image     = File:Bangkok Universit..Rangsit campus. - panoramio.jpg\n|image_name      = \n|staff           =\n|faculty         =\n|colors          = [[Orange (colour)|Orange]] & [[Purple]] {{color box|#FFA500}}{{color box|#800080}}\n|affiliation    = [[ASAIHL]]\n|coor            = {{coord|13|42|41.10|N|100|34|54.87|E|type:edu_region:TH|display=inline,title}}\n}}\n{{maplink|frame=yes|frame-width=240|zoom=13|type=point}}\n\n'''Bangkok University''' ({{lang-th|\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e01\u0e23\u0e38\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e1e}}), established in 1962, is one of the oldest and largest private, non-profit universities in Thailand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/en/about/history|title=History|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref> The main campus is in the [[Khlong Toei District|central business district]] of Bangkok. The university expanded its operation to a second campus in [[Rangsit, Thailand|Rangsit]], [[Pathum Thani Province]] to accommodate its rapid growth.\n\nThe university president is Mr Petch Osathanugrah (2016).<ref>{{cite web|title=Executive Officer|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/about-executive-officer.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425134627/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/about-executive-officer.html|archive-date=25 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Academic programs ==\nUsing Thai as the language of instruction, Bangkok University awards bachelor's degrees,<ref>{{cite web|title=Bachelor's Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-bachelor-degree-normal-program.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321133556/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-bachelor-degree-normal-program.html|archive-date=21 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> master's degrees,<ref>{{cite web|title=Master's Degrees|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-master-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427175333/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-master-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> and doctoral degrees.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctoral Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-doctoral-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321020014/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-doctoral-degree.html|archive-date=21 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The university also has an international program,<ref>{{cite web|title=International Program|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-programs.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427175327/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-programs.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> using English as the language of instruction. The international program awards bachelor's,<ref>{{cite web|title=International Program; Bachelor Degree/ \u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e25\u0e31\u0e22\u0e19\u0e32\u0e19\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e15\u0e34|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-bachelor-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427230047/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-bachelor-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> master's,<ref>{{cite web|title=Master Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-master-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321132301/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-master-degree.html|archive-date=21 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> and doctoral degrees.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doctoral Degree|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427230053/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Affiliates ==\n* BU Alumni<ref>{{cite web|title=BU Alumni|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/bu_alumni.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425152106/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/bu_alumni.html|archive-date=25 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Creative Entrepreneurship Development Institute<ref>{{cite web|title=Creative Entrepreneurship Development Institute|url=http://cedi.bu.ac.th/|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n* Bangkok University Research Center<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangkok University Research Center|url=http://bangkokpoll.bu.ac.th/|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n* The Institute for Knowledge and Innovation, Southeast Asia<ref>{{cite web|title=The Institute for Knowledge and Innovation, Southeast Asia|url=http://www.iki-sea.org/|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n*Center for Promotion of Human Resources\n*Institute of Research Promotion and Innovation Development\n*Institutional Research and Evaluation Office\n*Language Institute<ref>{{cite web|title=Language Institute|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427230053/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/academic-international-program-doctor-degree.html|archive-date=27 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*Law Center for Citizens\n\n== Campuses ==\nBangkok University has two campuses:\n\n=== City campus ===\nThe city campus (called ''Kluay Nam Thai Campus'', {{lang-th|\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e40\u0e02\u0e15\u0e01\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27\u0e22\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e44\u0e17}}) is in [[Phra Khanong, Khlong Toei|Phra Khanong Sub-district]], [[Khlong Toei District]].<ref name=\"Contact BU\">{{cite web|title=Contact BU|url=http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/contact-us.html|website=Bangkok University|accessdate=15 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425123026/http://www.bu.ac.th/eng/contact-us.html|archive-date=25 April 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> It occupies approximately 15,000 m<sup>2</sup>. International students attend this campus, as well as academics in special programs. It is the campus for most students in their third or fourth years. It is the location of the office of the university president, as well as the international college, the graduate school, and other faculties. There are laboratories, classrooms, seminar rooms, libraries, computer centre, and an indoor sports centre. An art gallery, the Bangkok University Gallery (BUG), opened on the campus in 2006. Bangkok University has decided to close this campus in the near future, and move all operations to the Rangsit campus, now already called \"main campus\".\n\n=== Rangsit campus ===\nThe Rangsit campus (\u0e27\u0e34\u0e17\u0e22\u0e32\u0e40\u0e02\u0e15\u0e23\u0e31\u0e07\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e15) is in Khlong Neung Sub-district [[Khlong Luang District]] of Pathum Thani Province.<ref name=\"Contact BU\" /> It is approximately fourteen kilometres north of [[Don Mueang International Airport]]. The campus is approximately 265,000 m<sup>2</sup> in size. Regular students in their first and second years study here, except that regular communication arts students (not international) study on this campus for four years. Also on the campus are the Bangkok University Stadium, home stadium of [[Bangkok University FC]], [[Thailand Premier League 2006]] champions, the Surat Osathanugrah Library, and Pongtip Osathanugrah Communication Arts Complex. The BU Southeast Asian Ceramics Museum, an important archaeological research facility, is on the Rangsit campus. The campus meets the [[ISO14000#ISO 14001 standard|ISO 14001 standard]], the first in Thailand to do so.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Portal|Thailand}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20171129124320/http://www2.bu.ac.th/eng/ Bangkok University]\n*{{Commonscat-inline|Bangkok University}}\n{{Universities in Thailand}}\n{{ASAIHL}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1962]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:Private universities and colleges in Thailand]]\n[[Category:1962 establishments in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Universities in Thailand]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangkok_University"}
